    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All thirteen credibility factors have been reviewed and the assessment team concludes that the simulation evidence, taken in aggregate, provides sufficient support for the intended regulatory submission. Discretization error and relevance factors are within acceptable margins for the primary pressure-head QoI, and the hemolysis index predictions are consistent with bench measurements at the three validated operating points. Remaining factor gaps are considered manageable given the conservative safety margins applied to the clinical threshold comparison.",
